news.title: Karnataka government tabled bill to levy property tax on unauthorised buildings
news.para: The municipalities Bill, tabled by urban development minister BS Suresh (Byrathi), seeks to fine officials up to Rs 50,000 and imprison them for 15 days if they fail to collect property tax dues.

news.title: E-khata integration to combat illegal registration of land in Karnataka
news.para: Byre Gowda was replying in the assembly to allegations by BJP’s SR Vishwanath, who accused sub-registrars of colluding with land sharks to illegally register agricultural land as residential and commercial plots.

news.title: Kajaria Ceramics' net profit dips 15.39% in Q1 FY25
news.para: Kajaria Ceramics' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,123.88 crore in Q1 FY25, a growth of 4.69 per cent from Rs 1,073.49 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP issues show-cause notices to 100 homes over illegal construction
news.para: Despite these notices, no satisfactory response has been received from any house owner, prompting the department to prepare restoration orders, said DTCP officials.

news.title: Sale of property of Rs 50 lakh or more involving multiple sellers, buyers to attract TDS
news.para: The government on Tuesday said that one per cent TDS will be applicable for transfer of immovable property involving multiple sellers or buyers wherein the aggregate consideration is Rs 50 lakh or more.

news.title: China's revenue from government land sales down 18.3% in H1 2024
news.para: Land sales, a key barometer tracking property sector momentum and local fiscal conditions, have fallen sharply since 2022 amid a prolonged property crisis and a sluggish economic growth.

news.title: Tamil Nadu CM launches housing projects worth Rs 541 crore
news.para: About 4,184 flats that were constructed on behalf of the Tamil Nadu Urban Habitat Development Board for Rs 541.32 crore and 1,459 flats for government servants

news.title: Your home loan process made easy: A step-by-step guide
news.para: Get a detailed overview of Bajaj Housing Finance Home Loan process. Follow a step-by-step guide to understand each stage and secure your dream home easily.

news.title: Budget 2024: FM offers Rs 2.2 lakh crore central assistance for PMAY-U homes in next five years
news.para: "This will include the central assistance of Rs 2.2 lakh crore in the next 5 years," she added, the government also plans to provide interest subsidy to facilitate loans at affordable rates, the minister said.

news.title: Akzo Nobel reports rise in profit by 1% in Q2 2024
news.para: Akzo Nobel reported adjusted earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortisation (EBITDA) of 400 million euros ($435.60 million).

news.title: Central government looks to lower duties for properties purchased by women
news.para: This reform will be made an essential component of urban development schemes, encourages states with high stamp duty to moderate rates for all, lower duties further for properties purchased by women," she said in the Budget speech.

news.title: Karnataka Cabinet nod for plan to split BBMP into multiple corporations
news.para: The bill, which is expected to be tabled in the ongoing session of the legislature, proposes significant changes to the administration of Bengaluru.

news.title: Bhutani Group picks up majority stake in WTC Noida in revenue-sharing deal
news.para: Five of these WTCs, located in Noida, Chandigarh, Gurugram, and Gift City are at various stages of construction and will require at least ₹3,000 crore to complete.

news.title: DTCP razes six illegal colonies in Alipur, Raisina and Bhondsi
news.para: According to officials, the operation was carried out with police support and resulted in the demolition of around 40 unauthorised structures, including shops, offices, guard rooms, entry gates, and road networks.

news.title: Self-certification enough for construction of small residential buildings in Tamil Nadu
news.para: Inaugurating the scheme on Monday under the Department of Housing and Urban Development, chief minister M K Stalin issued building permits to 10 beneficiaries.

news.title: Italy’s Proprium Capital Partners to invest $100 million in student housing sector
news.para: It will acquire and develop two purpose-built student accommodation (PBSA) projects to provide accommodation for more than 1,600 students in total in prime locations in the northern cities of Milan and Padua.
